    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe built-in ftplugin for Zig [auto-formats files on save by default](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/f660b794808ac809ee8cafe82ddd824840bc8e2c/runtime/ftplugin/zig.vim#L59C5-L59C5). In my opinion, this is really disruptive, making the editor do extra actions that the user never asked for.\r\n\r\nIt is also really hard to find the way to disable it since it is hidden in the depths of the pre-installed runtime files, which I personally did not even think to suspect at first.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n* Open a `.zig` file\r\n* Write some code in it\r\n* `:w`\r\n* The file gets inadvertently reformatted\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI would expect the file not to get reformatted on save by default because I never asked for it to be reformatted.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.9.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, vim 9.0.1676\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nManjaro Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.28.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nManjaro repository",
